        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 4:51PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monsey, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danbury, Shelton, New City, Ossining, New Canaan, Monsey, Nanuet,
Haverstraw, Tarrytown, Mount Kisco, Suffern, Nyack, Brewster,
Newtown, and Ridgefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
